23/02/2011
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The ruling VMRO-DPMNE wants to hold early elections as soon as possible, but without any preconditions, says party leader and Prime Minister Nikola Gruevski. On Tuesday (February 22nd), he urged Branko Crvenkovski, leader of the main opposition SDSM, to accept the idea without any strings attached. The opposition has set several conditions for holding early elections, chief among them including unfreezing A1 TV's bank accounts. (MIA, A1, Sitel, Kanal 5 - 22/02/11)
